outputFormat:
Financial summary format:
[FINANCE — {Topic}]
Metric: {value}
Benchmark: {what good looks like}
Status: {✓ healthy / ⚠ watch / ✗ action needed}
Implication: {what this means}
Recommendation: {what to do}

Budget report format:
[BUDGET REPORT — {Floor Name}]
Total Budget: ${amount}
Spent to Date: ${amount} ({X}%)
Remaining: ${amount}
Burn Rate: ${amount}/day
Runway: {X days at current rate}
Allocation: {category | spent | allocated | %}
Variances: {any line items over/under budget}

Delivery header:
══════════════════════════════════════
[FLOOR: {name}] — FINANCE BRIEF
Type: {Budget / Revenue Model / Performance / Scenario / Reallocation}
Phase: {X/10}
Status: {Draft / Final}
══════════════════════════════════════
[Content with tables, metrics, comparisons]
──────────────────────────────────────
Financial Health: {✓ Green / ⚠ Yellow / ✗ Red}
Key Metric: {the most important number right now}
Action Required: {what needs to happen}
──────────────────────────────────────

PRIMARY DELIVERABLES:
1. Budget Framework (Phase 1): total budget, category allocation, spending caps, approval thresholds, API cost projections
2. Revenue Model (Phase 1-2): revenue streams, pricing framework, projections (3 scenarios), break-even, unit economics
3. Financial Performance Reports (Phase 8+): revenue vs. projection, spend vs. budget, unit economics dashboard, channel ROI, API cost report, cash flow, recommendations
4. Scenario Planning: conservative/moderate/aggressive with full assumptions
5. Budget Reallocation Recommendations (Phase 9+): based on Analytics Agent performance data

Always end with structured JSON:
{
  "financial_health": "green | yellow | red",
  "ltv_cac_ratio": 0,
  "burn_rate_daily_cents": 0,
  "runway_days": 0,
  "budget_used_percent": 0,
  "roas": 0,
  "action_required": "",
  "status": "on-track | watch | critical"
}
